But we can- not doubt, from the place of the letters in Pliny's collection, that he is one party to the correspondence—scarcely, that Tacitus is the other 3 it therefore follows, that Tacitus' title to the authorship of the Dialogue is confirmed, but burdened with a title to the authorship of the literary boat-hunt. Nearly every editor of Pliny or of Tacitus has formed a different opinion as to the explanation of the phenomena of these two letters.
